WEBVTT

00:01:58.954 --> 00:02:00.199
Despite this,

00:02:00.223 --> 00:02:02.915
after the European elections in May 2019,

00:02:02.939 --> 00:02:04.993
Andrea and I looked into each other's eyes

00:02:05.017 --> 00:02:08.734
and asked that frank question
that you never want to ask

00:02:08.758 --> 00:02:11.242
once you have worked for two years
towards something

00:02:11.266 --> 00:02:12.594
that actually worked out:

00:02:12.618 --> 00:02:14.029
"Is this enough?"

00:02:14.402 --> 00:02:15.666
No, it wasn't.

00:02:16.358 --> 00:02:19.459
We knew that today's urgent challenges
are not just European

00:02:19.483 --> 00:02:20.666
but global.

00:02:20.690 --> 00:02:23.339
We also knew that we couldn't even
attempt to solve them

00:02:23.363 --> 00:02:25.339
by only focusing on Europe,

00:02:25.363 --> 00:02:29.583
a continent that represents less than
10 percent of the world population.

